net.sf.jguiraffe.di.impl.providers

Class SimpleBeanProviderTestHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jguiraffe.di.impl.providers.SimpleBeanProviderTestHelper

  • public class SimpleBeanProviderTestHelper
extends Object
    A helper class that provides some default functionality for testing simple bean providers, especially providers that use Invocation objects for creating bean instances. This class defines some constants and static utility methods that can be used by corresponding test classes.
    Version:
    $Id: SimpleBeanProviderTestHelper.java 205 2012-01-29 18:29:57Z oheger $
    Author:
    Oliver Heger

      • setUpDependencyProvider

        public static DependencyProvider setUpDependencyProvider(boolean replay)
        Creates a mock for a DependencyProvider, which is able to resolve the test class. The call for the loadClass() method is optional, i.e. if a ClassDedescription caches its value, this won't be a problem.
        Parameters:
        replay - a flag whether the replay() method is to be called
        Returns:
        the initialized mock object

      • setUpDepProviderForGetBean

        public static DependencyProvider setUpDepProviderForGetBean(BeanProvider provider)
        Creates a dependency provider mock object, which can be used for testing a getBean() operation. This mock expects calls to its getDependentBean() method. The return values for these calls are obtained from the given bean provider's dependencies.
        Parameters:
        provider - the bean provider
        Returns:
        the initialized mock object

      • checkTestInstance

        public static void checkTestInstance(Object o)
        Tests a newly created bean instance. This method checks whether the passed in object is an instance of ReflectionTestClass and whether its properties are correctly set.
        Parameters:
        o - the object to check
